RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 76. Maiden Claiming Purse 32000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000. (If deemed inadvisable to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the Tapeta Course at One Mile and Seventy Yards) (Rail at 35 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RECONNECTING was bumped at the start, had her heels clipped behind not long after, raced off the pace two wide, advanced three wide around the far turn, tipped out for clear sailing in upper stretch, kicked in and was up late. GREY PRINCESS was rank while racing three wide between foes, checked midway around the first turn, launched a four wide bid around the far turn, struck the front leaving the eighth pole, drifted out under left-handed urging and was caught in deep stretch. WAND was forced out nearing the first turn, angled in early on the bend, advanced three wide around the far turn, swung widest in upper stretch, closed strongly, steadied late and just missed second. AMOR SALVAJE bumped at the start, saved ground off the pace, angled five wide near the quarter pole, was bumped in upper stretch then rallied. SEEKINGBYTHESTORM set the pace in the three path around the first turn and the two path around the far turn, continued on the left lead in the lane, led past the eighth and weakened. BULLET VALENTINA raced up close inside and faded through the final furlong. OOPSIE DOOPSIE stalked the pace two and three wide and weakened. COLLECT A LIL clipped heels soon after the start, got out and was checked entering the first turn, angled in soon after, saved ground well back, swung out turning for home, bumped AMOR SALVAJE in upper stretch and improved position. KINDNESS IS FREE was unprepared for the start then bumped, chased the pace two wide around the first turn, and from the rail around the far turn and lacked a closing bid. MERRY GOLD raced off the early pace four wide, made a three middle move but came up empty in the lane. HEADING WEST broke inwardly and bumped the winner at the start, raced off the pace three and four wide and had no response. LADY BOURBON played no factor while racing two and three wide. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY IN THE STRETCH RUN AND FOUND NO REASON TO ALTER THE ORIGINAL ORDER OF FINISH.
